The body of a man was found in the Klein Olifants River near Vloed Street in Eastdene on Monday at about 19:30. Due to the heavy floods, the body was seen floating facedown along the river by a passer-by, who then contacted the police. Also read: Eyewitness: Man’s body recovered from Klein Olifants River, dragged over flooded low-water bridge  The dead man has been transported to the Middelburg Forensic Pathology Department for a post-mortem examination, and an investigation has been opened by the police. Anyone who might have a missing family member is urged to visit the Middelburg Police Station. • In January, the body of another man was also retrieved by police divers at the low-water bridge near Koppie Street.